* ============================================================
* MCC_TUPLE_BUFFER_OVERLAY_SHAKEDOWN.DTS
* Focus:
*  - Verify TUP / TUPLE become TABLE-buffer aware (overlay)
*  - Verify DBF not changed until COMMIT (TABLE ON)
*  - Verify TABLE OFF does direct writes
*
* Assumptions:
*  - MCC DBFs present
*  - STUDENTS has fields: SID, LNAME, FNAME, DOB, GENDER, MAJOR, ENROLL_D, GPA, EMAIL
* ============================================================

SET ECHO ON
ECHO ===== TUPLE BUFFER OVERLAY SHAKE-DOWN START =====
COLOR DEFAULT

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 0) Open tables
* ------------------------------------------------------------
SCHEMAS CLOSE
SCHEMAS OPEN DBF
SELECT STUDENTS
* USE STUDENTS

* Anchor on stable record (use same SID you’ve been using)
TOP
LOCATE FOR SID = 50000001
RECNO
TUP
TUPLE

ECHO -- Baseline (physical) -- 
LIST 2
TUP DOB
TUP ENROLL_D

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 1) TABLE ON: REPLACE buffers, TUP must show overlay immediately
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CASE 1: TABLE ON overlay appears in TUP immediately =====
TABLE ON

* Make a visible change (strings)
REPLACE FNAME WITH "ZZ_TUPBUF"
REPLACE LNAME WITH "YY_TUPBUF"

* Expected:
*  - TUP/TUPLE should show ZZ_TUPBUF / YY_TUPBUF immediately (buffer overlay)
*  - LIST should still show old physical values until COMMIT (unless LIST also became overlay-aware)
ECHO -- After buffered REPLACE (no COMMIT yet) --
TUP
TUPLE
LIST 1

* Show buffer contents (optional sanity)
TABLE BUFFER DUMP

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 2) TABLE ON: Date field buffered overlay (DOB + ENROLL_D)
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CASE 2: Buffered DATE overlay in TUP =====
REPLACE DOB WITH 19560214
REPLACE ENROLL_D WITH 20240923

ECHO -- After buffered date REPLACE (no COMMIT yet) --
TUP DOB
TUP ENROLL_D
TUP
TUPLE

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 3) TABLE ON: blank-date buffering (should overlay as blanks)
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CASE 3: Buffered blank-date overlay =====
REPLACE DOB WITH "        "

ECHO -- DOB should now show blank in TUP/TUPLE (no COMMIT) --
TUP DOB
TUP
TUPLE

* Restore DOB buffered to a real date so we can commit safely
REPLACE DOB WITH 19560213

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 4) COMMIT: physical DBF changes now match buffered values
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CASE 4: COMMIT applies buffered values to DBF =====
COMMIT

ECHO -- After COMMIT: TUP and LIST should match new values physically --
TUP
TUPLE
LIST 1

* Restore baseline physical values (so dataset doesn’t drift)
ECHO ===== RESTORE BASELINE (TABLE ON + COMMIT) =====
REPLACE LNAME WITH "Washington"
REPLACE FNAME WITH "George"
REPLACE DOB WITH 19560213
REPLACE ENROLL_D WITH 20240922
COMMIT

ECHO -- After baseline restore --
TUP
LIST 1

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 5) TABLE OFF: REPLACE should write directly (no buffering)
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CASE 5: TABLE OFF direct write behavior =====
TABLE OFF

REPLACE FNAME WITH "ZZ_OFF"
ECHO -- With TABLE OFF, physical should change immediately --
TUP
LIST 1

* Restore again (direct write)
REPLACE FNAME WITH "George"
ECHO -- Restored --
TUP
LIST 1

ECHO ===== TUPLE BUFFER OVERLAY SHAKE-DOWN END =====
